<section xml:id="DefFunc" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Definition of a Function</title>
    <p>
        In this section, we will definine a function and learn how to identify the
        input and output variables of graphs, tables, diagrams, and equations.
    </p>

    <definition xml:id="def-">
        <statement>
            <p>
                A <term>function</term>
                is a relationship between two variables for which a unique value of the <term>output</term>
                variable can be determined from a value of the <term>input</term>
                variable.
                In other words, a function is relation in which every input corresponds to exactly one output.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </definition>

